  "content_html": "<style>\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet{display:grid!important;gap:24px!important;max-width:1040px!important;color:#182230!important;font-size:17px!important;line-height:1.7!important}\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet h3{margin:0!important;padding:0 0 14px!important;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(15,118,110,.18)!important;color:#111827!important;font-size:28px!important;line-height:1.2!important;font-weight:900!important;letter-spacing:0!important}\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet h4{display:flex!important;align-items:center!important;gap:10px!important;margin:12px 0 0!important;color:#111827!important;font-size:20px!important;line-height:1.3!important;font-weight:900!important;letter-spacing:0!important}\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet h4::before{content:\"\"!important;width:8px!important;height:26px!important;border-radius:999px!important;background:#0f766e!important;box-shadow:0 0 0 4px rgba(15,118,110,.1)!important}\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .def-box,.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .ex-box,.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .note-box,.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .formula-box{position:relative!important;display:block!important;width:100%!important;max-width:100%!important;margin:0!important;padding:50px 24px 22px!important;border:1px solid rgba(17,24,39,.1)!important;border-radius:8px!important;background:#fff!important;color:#182230!important;box-shadow:0 18px 42px rgba(15,23,42,.08)!important;font-family:Inter,\"Noto Sans\",system-ui,sans-serif!important;text-align:left!important;overflow:hidden!important}\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .def-box::before,.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .ex-box::before,.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .note-box::before,.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .formula-box::before{position:absolute!important;top:16px!important;left:22px!important;display:inline-flex!important;align-items:center!important;min-height:24px!important;padding:0 10px!important;border-radius:999px!important;font-size:12px!important;font-weight:900!important;letter-spacing:.04em!important;text-transform:uppercase!important}\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .def-box::before{content:\"Concept\"!important;background:#eef2ff!important;color:#3730a3!important}\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .ex-box::before{content:\"Example\"!important;background:#ecfeff!important;color:#155e75!important}\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .note-box::before{content:\"Key takeaway\"!important;background:#ecfdf5!important;color:#047857!important}\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .formula-box::before{content:\"Process\"!important;background:#fff7ed!important;color:#9a3412!important}\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .def-box{border-left:4px solid #4f46e5!important}\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .ex-box{border-left:4px solid #0891b2!important}\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .note-box{border-left:4px solid #059669!important}\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .formula-box{border-left:4px solid #ea580c!important;background:#fffaf5!important}\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .card-title{display:flex!important;align-items:baseline!important;gap:10px!important;flex-wrap:wrap!important;margin:0 0 12px!important;color:#101828!important;font-size:18px!important;line-height:1.35!important;font-weight:900!important}\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .card-title span{color:#475467!important;font-size:13px!important;font-weight:900!important;text-transform:uppercase!important;letter-spacing:.04em!important}\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet p{max-width:100%!important;margin:0 0 12px!important;color:#344054!important;line-height:1.72!important}\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet p:last-child{margin-bottom:0!important}\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet strong{color:#101828!important;font-weight:900!important}\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet b{color:#111827!important;font-weight:900!important}\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .axiom-grid,.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .vector-set,.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .system-grid{display:grid!important;gap:10px!important;margin-top:14px!important}\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .axiom-grid{grid-template-columns:repeat(2,minmax(0,1fr))!important}\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .axiom-grid div,.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .vector-set span,.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .system-grid div{padding:12px 14px!important;border:1px solid rgba(17,24,39,.08)!important;border-radius:8px!important;background:#f8fafc!important;color:#344054!important}\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .axiom-grid b,.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .term-label{display:block!important;margin-bottom:4px!important;color:#101828!important;font-family:Inter,\"Noto Sans\",system-ui,sans-serif!important;font-size:14px!important;font-weight:900!important}\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .term-list{display:grid!important;gap:12px!important}\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .term-list>div{padding:12px 14px!important;border:1px solid rgba(17,24,39,.08)!important;border-radius:8px!important;background:#f8fafc!important}\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .math-line{display:block!important;color:#111827!important;font-family:\"Cambria Math\",Cambria,\"Times New Roman\",serif!important;font-size:18px!important;line-height:1.65!important;white-space:normal!important;word-break:normal!important;overflow-wrap:normal!important}.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .inline-math{display:inline!important;color:#111827!important;font-family:\"Cambria Math\",Cambria,\"Times New Roman\",serif!important;font-size:1.02em!important;line-height:inherit!important;white-space:nowrap!important}\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .example-question{font-size:18px!important;color:#182230!important}\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .proof-row,.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .result-row{display:flex!important;align-items:flex-start!important;gap:10px!important;flex-wrap:wrap!important;margin-top:12px!important;padding:12px 14px!important;border-radius:8px!important;background:#f8fafc!important;color:#344054!important}\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .tag{display:inline-flex!important;align-items:center!important;min-height:24px!important;padding:0 9px!important;border-radius:999px!important;background:#ecfeff!important;color:#155e75!important;font-size:12px!important;font-weight:900!important;text-transform:uppercase!important;letter-spacing:.04em!important}\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .result-pill{display:inline-flex!important;align-items:center!important;padding:3px 10px!important;border-radius:999px!important;background:#ecfdf5!important;color:#047857!important;font-weight:900!important}\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .process-steps{display:grid!important;gap:12px!important;margin-top:4px!important}\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .process-step{display:grid!important;grid-template-columns:auto minmax(0,1fr)!important;gap:10px 14px!important;align-items:start!important;padding:14px!important;border:1px solid rgba(234,88,12,.14)!important;border-radius:8px!important;background:#fff!important}\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .step-index{display:inline-flex!important;align-items:center!important;justify-content:center!important;width:30px!important;height:30px!important;border-radius:999px!important;background:#fff7ed!important;color:#9a3412!important;font-weight:900!important}\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .step-body{display:grid!important;gap:6px!important;min-width:0!important}\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .note-box{font-weight:700!important}\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .math-frac{display:inline-grid!important;grid-template-rows:auto auto!important;place-items:center!important;vertical-align:middle!important;font-family:\"Cambria Math\",Cambria,\"Times New Roman\",serif!important;line-height:1.05!important;margin:0 .12em!important}\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .math-frac>span{display:block!important;padding:.04em .25em!important;white-space:nowrap!important}\n.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .math-frac>span:first-child{width:100%!important;border-bottom:1.5px solid currentColor!important;text-align:center!important}\n@media (max-width:720px){.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet{gap:18px!important;font-size:16px!important}.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet h3{font-size:24px!important}.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .def-box,.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .ex-box,.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .note-box,.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .formula-box{padding:46px 16px 18px!important}.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .axiom-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr!important}.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .math-line{font-size:16px!important}.lesson-content .content-body .vector-space-sheet .process-step{grid-template-columns:1fr!important}}\n</style>\n<div class=\"vector-space-sheet\">\n<h3>2.2 Vector Spaces</h3>\n<div class=\"def-box\">\n<div class=\"card-title\"><span>Definition 2.9</span><strong>Vector Space</strong></div>\n<p>A set <b>V</b> closed under addition and scalar multiplication, satisfying eight axioms.</p>\n<div class=\"axiom-grid\">\n<div><b>Addition axioms</b>Associativity, null vector <span class=\"inline-math\">0</span>, inverse <span class=\"inline-math\">−u</span>, and commutativity.</div>\n<div><b>Scalar multiplication axioms</b>Distributivity, associativity, and unit scalar <span class=\"inline-math\">1·u = u</span>.</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"ex-box\">\n<div class=\"card-title\"><span>Example 2.5</span><strong>Solutions of AX = 0</strong></div>\n<p>Solutions <b>X</b> of <span class=\"inline-math\">AX = 0</span> form a vector space.</p>\n<div class=\"proof-row\"><span class=\"tag\">Proof</span><span>If <span class=\"inline-math\">AX₁ = 0</span> and <span class=\"inline-math\">AX₂ = 0</span>, then <span class=\"inline-math\">A(X₁ + X₂) = 0</span> and <span class=\"inline-math\">A(λX₁) = 0</span>.</span></div>\n<div class=\"result-row\"><span class=\"tag\">Not a space</span><span>Solutions of <span class=\"inline-math\">AX = B</span> with <span class=\"inline-math\">B ≠ 0</span> do not form a vector space because <span class=\"inline-math\">A(X₁ + X₂) = 2B ≠ B</span>.</span></div>\n</div>\n\n<h4>Linear Independence</h4>\n<div class=\"def-box\">\n<div class=\"term-list\">\n<div><span class=\"term-label\">Linear combination</span><span class=\"math-line\">k₁u₁ + k₂u₂ + ... + kₘuₘ</span></div>\n<div><span class=\"term-label\">Linearly independent</span><span class=\"math-line\">k₁u₁ + ... + kₘuₘ = 0 implies k₁ = k₂ = ... = kₘ = 0.</span></div>\n<div><span class=\"term-label\">Linearly dependent</span>Some non-trivial combination equals zero.</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"ex-box\">\n<div class=\"card-title\"><span>Example 2.8</span><strong>Linear combination check</strong></div>\n<p class=\"example-question\">Can <span class=\"inline-math\">v = i − k</span> be written as a linear combination of these vectors?</p>\n<div class=\"vector-set\">\n<span class=\"math-line\">u₁ = i + 2j + 3k</span>\n<span class=\"math-line\">u₂ = −i + j + k</span>\n<span class=\"math-line\">u₃ = j + k</span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"system-grid\">\n<div><span class=\"term-label\">System</span><span class=\"math-line\">1 = a − b</span><span class=\"math-line\">0 = 2a + b + c</span><span class=\"math-line\">−1 = 3a + b + c</span></div>\n<div><span class=\"term-label\">Gaussian elimination</span><span class=\"result-pill\">a = −1, b = −2, c = 4</span><span>Yes, <b>v</b> is linearly representable.</span></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<h4>Basis and Dimension</h4>\n<div class=\"def-box\">\n<div class=\"term-list\">\n<div><span class=\"term-label\">Basis</span>A set of linearly independent vectors that span the entire space.</div>\n<div><span class=\"term-label\">Dimension</span>Number of vectors in any basis.</div>\n<div><span class=\"term-label\">Standard basis of ℝ³</span><span class=\"math-line\">{i, j, k}</span><span>Dimension 3.</span></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<h4>2.3.4 Orthogonal and Orthonormal Basis</h4>\n<div class=\"def-box\">\n<div class=\"term-list\">\n<div><span class=\"term-label\">Orthogonal basis</span>All basis vectors are mutually perpendicular, so their dot product is zero.</div>\n<div><span class=\"term-label\">Orthonormal basis</span>Orthogonal and each vector has unit magnitude: <span class=\"inline-math\">|eᵢ| = 1</span></div>\n<div><span class=\"term-label\">Standard basis</span><span class=\"math-line\">{i, j, k}</span> is orthonormal.</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<h4>2.3.5 Gram-Schmidt Process</h4>\n<p>Converts any linearly independent set <span class=\"inline-math\">{v₁, v₂, ...}</span> into an orthonormal basis <span class=\"inline-math\">{e₁, e₂, ...}</span>.</p>\n<div class=\"formula-box\">\n<div class=\"process-steps\">\n<div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-index\">1</span><div class=\"step-body\"><span class=\"math-line\">u₁ = v₁</span><span class=\"math-line\">e₁ = <span class=\"math-frac\"><span>u₁</span><span>|u₁|</span></span></span></div></div>\n<div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-index\">2</span><div class=\"step-body\"><span class=\"math-line\">u₂ = v₂ − (v₂·e₁)e₁</span><span class=\"math-line\">e₂ = <span class=\"math-frac\"><span>u₂</span><span>|u₂|</span></span></span></div></div>\n<div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-index\">3</span><div class=\"step-body\"><span class=\"math-line\">u₃ = v₃ − (v₃·e₁)e₁ − (v₃·e₂)e₂</span><span class=\"math-line\">e₃ = <span class=\"math-frac\"><span>u₃</span><span>|u₃|</span></span></span></div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"note-box\">At each step: subtract projections onto already-found orthonormal vectors, then normalize. The result is a set of mutually perpendicular unit vectors spanning the same space.</div>\n</div>",
